                        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">The Importance of Politeness</h2>\
                        <p class="text-gray-700">Albanians generally value politeness and respect, especially in initial interactions or with elders. Using formal "Ju" (you plural/formal) when addressing someone you don't know well or who is older is a good practice, though "Ti" (you singular/informal) is common among peers and younger people. When in doubt, it's safer to start with "Ju."</p>\
