                        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-6">Eye Contact & Handshakes</h2>\
                        <p class="text-gray-700">Direct eye contact during conversation is seen as a sign of sincerity and engagement. When meeting someone for the first time, a firm handshake is standard. Among close friends and family, air kisses on both cheeks are common (starting with the right cheek, then the left).</p>\
\
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-6">Initial Questions</h2>\
                        <p class="text-gray-700">After greetings, it's common to ask "Si je?" (How are you?) or "Si jeni?" (How are you? - formal/plural). Showing interest in the other person's well-being is a sign of good manners. Don't be surprised if the conversation quickly moves to family, as family is a cornerstone of Albanian society.</p>\
