                        <p class="text-gray-700">Historically, traditional gender roles were quite defined, with men often being the public face of the family and women managing the household. While modern Albanian society, especially in urban areas, is seeing these roles evolve rapidly, some traditional expectations may still be present, particularly in rural regions. Being aware of these historical contexts can provide insight into certain social dynamics, though it's important to approach individuals without preconceived notions.</p>\
