                        </ul>\
\
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-6">Tips for More Natural Pronunciation</h2>\
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">\
                            <li><strong>Shadowing:</strong> Listen to native Albanian speakers (e.g., in simple videos or audio lessons) and try to repeat exactly what they say, mimicking their rhythm, intonation, and connection of words.</li>\
                            <li><strong>Focus on Syllable Stress:</strong> While Albanian stress can be tricky, generally words are stressed on the second to last syllable. Pay attention to this for new vocabulary.</li>\
                            <li><strong>Record Yourself:</strong> Record yourself saying sentences from the example section and compare them to a native speaker's pronunciation. This helps you identify areas for improvement.</li>\
